trated%20a%20warm%20and%20fuzzy%20public%20send-off%2C%20thanking%20Musk%20for%20his%20service%20and%20providing%20a%20sensible%20explanation%20for%20his%20departure%E2%80%94in%20this%20case%2C%20that%20the%20billionaire%20was%20going%20back%20to%20focusing%20on%20his%20work%20at%20the%20multiple%20companies%20he%20helms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20common%20explanations%20are%20that%20the%20fired%20individual%20has%20decided%20to%20pursue%20other%20career%20opportunities%2C%20spend%20time%20with%20family%2C%20or%20engage%20in%20philanthropic%20endeavors.%20This%20tactic%20is%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20both%20the%20departee's%20reputation%20and%20that%20of%20the%20employer%20showing%20him%20or%20her%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20come%20up%20with%20a%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anna%20A.%20Tavis%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20human%20capital%20management%20department%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20School%20of%20Professional%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20is%20to%20avoid%20hurting%20the%20outgoing%20hotshot's%20chances%20of%20landing%20a%20new%20gig%20and%20the%20company's%20ability%20to%20find%20a%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20question%20of%2C%20how%20do%20we%20save%20face%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220f000a7-79bf-46b5-8aa0-28cb2ba71181%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGive%20people%20something%20else%20to%20talk%20about%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20should%20also%20aim%20to%20draw%20people's%20attention%20elsewhere%2C%20Placone%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20Trump's%20strategies%20that%20often%20works%20is%20you%20just%20flood%20communication%20channels%20with%20other%20stuff%2C%20stuff%20you%20perceive%20is%20more%20favorable%20to%20your%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20try%20to%20take%20some%20control%20by%20giving%20as%20many%20potential%20stories%20as%20possible%20so%20people%20don't%20home%20in%20on%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20did%20make%20some%20big%20announcements%20this%20week%2C%20including%20travel%20bans%20on%20several%20African%20countries%2C%20but%20leadership%20experts%20say%20the%20president%20also%20erred%20by%20openly%20rebuking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-give-negative-feedback-to-your-boss-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMusk's%20harsh%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20his%20signature%20tax%20bill%20on%20X.%20This%20kicked%20off%20the%20back-and-forth%20squabble%20that%20captured%20the%20world's%20attention%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20need%20for%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Placone%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20these%20high-profile%20situations%2C%20you%20want%20to%20say%20as%20little%20as%20possible.%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20add%20weight%20to%20the%20argument%20the%20other%20is%20putting%20forth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20instead%20kept%20quiet%2C%20Musk%20would%20have%20been%20more%20likely%20to%20stick%20with%20critiquing%20the%20bill%20rather%20than%20upping%20the%20ante%20by%20accusing%20the%20president%20of%20illicit%20behavior%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would've%20eventually%20fizzled%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Placone%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ae7b9be4-9956-4e59-9dbf-b4fb31118253%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20some%20A-list%20hires%20don't%20last%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20most%20commonly%20end%20up%20quickly%20sacking%20flashy%20new%20recruits%20because%20they%20aren't%20as%20talented%20as%20advertised%20or%20they%20insist%20on%20working%20in%20a%20way%20that%20doesn't%20align%20with%20a%20company's%20culture%2C%20Tavis%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20even%20happens%20at%20the%20very%20top%20of%20the%20corporate%20ladder.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20chief%20executives%20of%20Barnes%20%26amp%3B%20Noble%2C%20Starbucks%2C%20and%20CNN%20were%20pushed%20out%20of%20their%20jobs%20after%20brief%20tenures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%20they're%20overestimating%20their%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20of%20people%20with%20a%20reputation%20for%20being%20above%20the%20fray%2C%20adding%20that%20due%20to%20the%20current%20tight%20labor%20market%2C%20notable%20departures%20are%20likely%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Faycurry%2C%20CEO%20of%20artificial-intelligence%20and%20nutrition%20startup%20Fay%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20can%20relate.%20Last%20year%2C%20he%20hired%20a%20well-known%20rainmaker%20after%20a%20lengthy%20courtship%20only%20to%20quickly%20conclude%20that%20the%20person%20wasn't%20a%20good%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20bad%20blood%2C%20Faycurry%20said%20he%20tried%20making%20it%20seem%20as%20if%20it%20was%20the%20individual's%20decision%20to%20leave%20by%20pointing%20out%20how%20much%20they%20disagreed%20on%20core%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20person%20ended%20up%20exiting%20themselves%26quot%3B%20without%20any%20hard%20feelings%2C%20Faycurry%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20was%20relieved%20because%20his%20main%20concern%20was%20being%20able%20to%20refill%20the%20position%20with%20a%20better-aligned%20A-list%20professional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20person%20is%20influential%20in%20a%20talent%20pool%20you%20want%20to%20recruit%20people%20from%20in%20the%20future%2C%20there's%20no%20benefit%20to%20having%20a%20relationship%20fall%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Faycurry%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20never%20truly%20parting%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-trump-how-to-fire-high-profile-employee-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1749295141000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F684358523d5881a51c1af711%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-trump-how-to-fire-high-profile-employee-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20publ