22%3Elate%201800s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20became%20a%20slur%20and%20was%20used%20to%20insult%20LGBTQ%2B%20people%2C%20famously%20appearing%20during%20Oscar%20Wilde%E2%80%99s%20trial%20in%201894.%20After%20the%201969%20Stonewall%20Riots%2C%20activists%20began%20reclaiming%20%E2%80%9Cqueer%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20term%20of%20empowerment%20and%20unity.%20By%20the%201990s%20and%20early%202000s%2C%20it%20appeared%20in%20pop%20culture%2C%20like%20the%20show%20%3Cem%3EQueer%20As%20Folk%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20started%20to%20be%20embraced%20more%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20queer%20is%20an%20umbrella%20term%20for%20many%20LGBTQ%2B%20identities.%20It%20is%20a%20way%20to%20express%20fluidity%20in%20gender%20and%20sexuality%20that%20reflects%20resistance%20and%20inclusivity.%20Some%20still%20find%20it%20hard%20to%20use%20because%20of%20its%20past%20as%20a%20slur%2C%20but%20for%20many%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20powerful%20way%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20who%20I%20am!%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20acronym%20LGBTQ%2B%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9CQ%E2%80%9D%20stands%20for%20queer%20and%2For%20questioning.%20It%20reflects%20a%20broad%20spectrum%20of%20identities%2C%20while%20%E2%80%9Cquestioning%E2%80%9D%20refers%20to%20individuals%20exploring%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F352820%2Ffathers-day-gay-couple-adoption-srivatsan-saravanan-sendhan-canada-chennai-lgbtq-pride-month%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esexual%20orientation%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20gender%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENonbinary%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonbinary%20is%20a%20term%20some%20people%20use%20when%20their%20gender%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20fit%20into%20the%20categories%20of%20%E2%80%9Cman%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cwoman.%E2%80%9D%20They%20might%20feel%20like%20both%2C%20neither%2C%20or%20something%20else%20entirely.%20Some%20nonbinary%20people%20also%20identify%20as%20transgender%2C%20b